{
  "texts": [
    "The connected components ⟨q⟩ ∈ π 0 (I) such that n ⟨q⟩ ̸ = 0 are called the active circles or active exponents.",
    "If i ∈ I d and ⟨q⟩ is the circle with i ∈ ⟨q⟩, we sometimes write Θ(i):= Θ(⟨q⟩) (this is the above number n i).",
    "Let us again fix a base direction d ∈ ∂ and denote by ρ ∈ Aut(V d) the monodromy",
    "Since the grading is locally constant, the monodromy of V has to be compatible with the monodromy of I, that is",
    ", for any i ∈ I d."
  ]
}